post_text:
National Donut Day Fun Fact!

Did you know? This day honors the group's "donut lassies," who served treats and provided assistance to soldiers on the front lines during World War I. (And this isn't to be confused with National Doughnut Day, which is in November and celebrates the actual food.)

Doughnuts have been around since long before the First World War, and we have the Dutch to thank for them. The Dutch would make "olykoek," which translates to oily cake. The first Dutch doughnuts didn't have a hole, but they were fried in hot oil and the dough was sweet.

It wasn't until 1847 that the holed-out doughnut we know and love today appeared. Hanson Gregory, 16 at the time, claimed credit. Sick of doughnuts with a raw center, he used a pepper pot to punch out holes to help his doughnuts cook more evenly.

Doughnuts have been around since long before the First World War, and we have the Dutch to thank for them. The Dutch would make "olykoek," which translates to oily cake. The first Dutch doughnuts didn't have a hole, but they were fried in hot oil and the dough was sweet.

It wasn't until 1847 that the holed-out doughnut we know and love today appeared. Hanson Gregory, 16 at the time, claimed credit. Sick of doughnuts with a raw center, he used a pepper pot to punch out holes to help his doughnuts cook more evenly.

May 26 at 10:18 AM ·

🔸 Post a picture of your child reading something interesting, other than a book
🔸 Post a picture of your child reading to a sibling, pet, or other interesting buddy (consider social distancing as appropriate)

post_text:
Beginning Monday March 30, PBS Reno we will provide at-home learning programs on our over-the-air channel 5.3. This digital channel can be accessed over the air, for free. Viewers do not need a cable or satellite subscription to see these programs over the air. The programs will be broadcast each Monday-Friday from 8am-4pm to closely match the regular school day. Our programs for children pre-k-3rd grade will remain on our main channel, 5.1 on their regular schedule between the hours of 6am-1pm.

More information is available at PBSReno.org/CampCuriosity. We have a hotline staffed to help parents, children and viewers with any issues they may have in accessing our content. That number is 775-600-0537.

Churchill County School District
March 20 at 1:31 PM ·

Our entire ChurchillCSD team has been learning and adjusting over the last five days to meet the needs of all of our students. Here is a highlight reel of all of the amazing things our staff has been able to accomplish during this time of Learning From a Distance. We will continue to work hard to serve the youth of our community!
text:
See what Churchill County School District has been doing the past few days for kids.

Churchill County School District
March 20 at 1:31 PM ·

Our entire ChurchillCSD team has been learning and adjusting over the last five days to meet the needs of all of our students. Here is a highlight reel of all of the amazing things our staff has been able to accomplish during this time of Learning From a Distance. We will continue to work hard to serve the youth of our community!

post_text: The Clark County School District is working to find ways to offer education to students outside the classroom. They have uploaded some Student Learning Extension Opportunities to CCSD.net and they hope to continue adding additional resources throughout the closures.
text: The Clark County School District is working to find ways to offer education to students outside the classroom. They have uploaded some Student Learning Extension Opportunities to CCSD.net and they hope to continue adding additional resources throughout the closures.

post_text: Clark County School District now has more resources available to families as they continue working to ensure students receive meals during the school closure. They are now offering food at 28 locations and are grateful to numerous community partners including Three Square Food Bank, The Just One Project, Station Casinos and others who have stepped up to offer meals to students. Please visit CCSD.net for more information on current available food-site locations as they continue to add more.

post_text: Starting Wednesday, March 18th, Douglas County School District will be serving food service meals.
shared_text:
Douglas County School District
March 17 at 5:47 PM ·

A revised flyer with additional information and menu for our Food Service Meals that will begin tomorrow, March 18th. We do want to clarify that students do not have to be with their parents when the meals are picked up, but only immediate family members can pick up meals for their student(s). The auto-dialer message mistakenly indicated students had to be present!
